## BUILD RULES — Every Task

### Rule 1: Read Before Build
Before building anything new:
1. Check if it exists in GitHub docs
2. If documented: follow the documented pattern exactly
3. If NOT documented: do read-only audit first
4. Report audit findings to Eric
5. Wait for go-ahead before writing a single node

### Rule 2: State Your Plan First
Before writing any Blueprint nodes:
```
My plan for [task]:
1. [exact node 1]
2. [exact node 2]
3. [exact node 3]
Parent class: [parent]
Path: [full /Game/ path]
Compile strategy: [what I'll do if compile fails]
```
Wait for Eric to say "go ahead" before building.

### Rule 3: One Compile Attempt Per Approach
- Compile once
- If it fails: report the exact error, stop
- Do not attempt silent self-fixes
- Do not try a different approach without telling Eric

### Rule 4: Never Modify Core FCS
These are off-limits without explicit Eric approval:
- BP_PlayerCharacter core event graphs
- BP_AI_Parent core event graphs
- BP_SaveGame core variables
- Any FCS widget without understanding its dependencies
- Any FCS component that other Blueprints depend on

### Rule 5: Test Before Moving On
Every task has success criteria.
Do not call a task complete until ALL criteria are met.
Report each criterion result individually.

